The 1GS protein crystallized in the space group P61 with a monomer in the asymmetric unit and its structure was solved at the resolution of 1.1 Å (Table 1
). Each of the three carbohydrate binding pockets of this form of mGRFT was occupied by molecules present in the crystallization and cryoprotection solutions. Pocket 1 (Ziólkowska et al., 2006), adjacent to Asp112, contained a glycerol molecule. Pocket 2, near Asp30, was filled by the terminal carboxylate group belonging to a symmetry-related molecule (Figure 2B), whereas pocket 3, near Asp70, contained two water molecules. The 2GS mGRFT crystallized in the space group P6522 and the structure was solved at 1.7 Å (Table 1). Each of the potential carbohydrate-binding pockets contained a glycerol molecule. Electron density for the inserted sequences on both of these mGRFT molecules were clearly seen in the |Fo|-|Fc| maps (Figure 3
). As predicted, these insertions led to formation of loops, allowing the first 16 amino acids to complete the β-prism fold of the same molecule.
